<article>

<p>
Authorities continue to investigate yesterday's fire that destroyed the abandoned
Cooper Textile Mill shortly after midnight. Local residents reported hearing
what several witnesses described as "metal striking stone" moments before the
first flames became visible.
</p>

<p>
County Fire Chief Harold Bennett stated that investigators have not yet
determined the cause of the blaze. Seven bodies were reportedly recovered,
although officials declined to identify the victims pending notification of
their families.
</p>

<p>
Sheriff's deputies have asked residents to avoid the area while investigators
continue their examination of the site.
</p>

